I agree that this would be a big improvement. It should be noted that, currently, ELB security groups are in the format {{euca-internal-<accountnumber>-<lbname>}}. The group information can also be garnered with {{eulb-describe-lbs --show-long}}

{code}
[12:00:50] [b-13 | 10.111.1.13]: eulb-describe-lbs --show-long
LOAD_BALANCER	new-lb	new-lb-407092041668.lb.b-13.autoqa.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com			{interval=30,target=TCP:80,timeout=5,healthy-threshold=3,unhealthy-threshold=2}	PARTI00				{protocol=HTTP,lb-port=80,instance-port=80}					{owner-alias=495375389014,group-name=euca-internal-407092041668-new-lb}		2014-05-30T19:00:38.099Z
{code}
